itemDescription: British Bletchley Park code breaker and historian (1922-2020)

wikipedia_page.main: Ailsa Maxwell (16 December 1922 - 10 February 2020) was a British Bletchley Park code breaker and historian.

link_mentions.page: List of women in Bletchley Park

response: She gained a place at Edinburgh University to study history. Someone at the university must have spotted her talents as she was invited to attend an interview for an unspecified job. The interview was in London and there she learnt that she was being recruited to work at Bletchley Park. She was interviewed by the Director of Military Intelligence. A fellow student of History at her university, Ailsa Maxwell, also accepted a similar offer.
